  "texts": [
    "The maximum weight is associated with the channel features that effectively differentiate between the objects in the scene, while the minimum weight is associated with the channel features that cannot effectively differentiate between the objects in the scene.",
    "The results depicted in Fig. 11 indicate that the network which was augmented with channel attention can effectively extract essential information from these scenes.",
    "The primary objects present in each scene are precisely captured, which greatly assists in the classification of the scenes.",
    "Hence, channel-wise attention was implemented to readjust the weights of multi-scale features that were extracted using the residual network.",
    "The feature maps that have a direct impact on the ground-truth label are assigned the highest attention weights, while the feature maps that contain irrelevant or misleading information are given the lowest attention weights."
  ],
